Now, aside from Sun Bojun
who's on the run,

53
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:16,140
the Dragon Unleashed
drug trafficking ring

54
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:17,460
has basically been wiped out.

55
00:04:23,370 --> 00:04:25,520
[Mr. Jiang]

56
00:04:26,660 --> 00:04:27,420
Sheng

57
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:29,860
heard this name during the negotiations

58
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:30,980
between Han Weidong and Sanmahu.

59
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,940
Both sides were wary of this person.

60
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:34,340
His existence also explains

61
00:04:34,340 --> 00:04:36,140
why there were so many doubts before.

62
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:39,260
Dragon Unleashed's gang
and Sanmahu's gang

63
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:39,860
have been fighting

64
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:40,780
yet negotiating all along.

65
00:04:40,980 --> 00:04:42,100
That's because there was

66
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:44,180
always someone behind the scenes
controlling them.

67
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:48,660
I feel sorry

68
00:04:48,660 --> 00:04:50,180
for what happened to Mr. Han.

69
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,060
I've been under him for many years.

70
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:53,420
He's always been good to me.

71
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:57,180
But he made mistakes.

72
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:59,980
And mistakes

73
00:05:00,980 --> 00:05:02,900
come with consequences.

74
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:04,700
With Mr. Han gone,

75
00:05:04,940 --> 00:05:06,060
there's a big gap left

76
00:05:06,620 --> 00:05:08,380
in your operation.

77
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:09,940
Mr. Wang,

78
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:12,100
I heard you used to be

79
00:05:12,660 --> 00:05:14,180
a straight-up businessman

80
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:17,580
and you were never

81
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:19,660
involved in anything this risky.

82
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:21,580
How about this?

83
00:05:21,940 --> 00:05:23,860
Why not hand over

84
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:26,220
all their previous business to me?

85
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:30,380
That's thoughtful of you.

86
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:33,140
I've been scratching my head over this.

87
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:35,260
I need to find someone to take over.

88
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:37,540
You know Xiatong so well.

89
00:05:38,180 --> 00:05:39,140
You'd be

90
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:40,620
the right fit.

91
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,340
Exactly.

92
00:05:42,820 --> 00:05:43,700
Don't worry.

93
00:05:52,580 --> 00:05:53,860
Rest assured, Mr. Wang.

94
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:56,940
You'll get every penny

95
00:05:57,980 --> 00:05:59,380
of your cut.

96
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:02,900
When Mr. Jiang called me, he said

97
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:05,380
business decisions are mine to make.

98
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,860
If I don't want to do it,
I hand it over.

99
00:06:08,860 --> 00:06:10,540
Once you take over,

100
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:13,500
you'll soon be the king
of Xiatong's underworld.

101
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:15,020
You can do whatever you want.

102
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,020
But there's one thing

103
00:06:17,340 --> 00:06:18,420
you absolutely can't touch.

104
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:19,820
What is it? Please tell me.

105
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:23,460
Mr. Jiang says you can't

106
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:25,420
lay a finger on Tu Hongjiang.

107
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:28,900
So Mr. Jiang wants to

108
00:06:29,980 --> 00:06:31,020
let him off the hook?

109
00:06:31,580 --> 00:06:32,860
Of course not.

110
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:35,180
He just doesn't think

111
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:38,220
you're qualified to take him on yet.

112
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,740
I'm not qualified?

113
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,300
I don't like the sound of that.

114
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:45,940
I've been dealing with him for 20 years.

115
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,340
Let me tell you,

116
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,700
in Xiatong,

117
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:49,860
no one

118
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:51,660
can outplay him except me!

119
00:06:51,860 --> 00:06:53,260
Don't be mad.

120
00:06:53,540 --> 00:06:54,940
I'm just passing along the message.

121
00:06:55,180 --> 00:06:56,660
If you disagree,

122
00:06:57,020 --> 00:06:59,060
you can take it up with Mr. Jiang.

123
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:02,700
My apologies.

124
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:04,020
Sorry about that.

125
00:07:05,660 --> 00:07:07,780
If Mr. Jiang says

126
00:07:08,780 --> 00:07:09,660
leave him alone,

127
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:10,980
then I'll

128
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:12,780
leave him alone.

129
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:13,820
Come on.

130
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:19,460
To our pleasant partnership.

131
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:54,020
[Xin]

132
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:54,820
Xin,

133
00:07:56,020 --> 00:07:57,540
by the time you read this,

134
00:07:58,660 --> 00:08:00,180
I'll be gone.

135
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:04,460
There's a ledger
in the drawer of the shrine

136
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:05,700
at our old place.

137
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,980
It records all the financial aid

138
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:12,140
we've given to families of officers
in need over the years.

139
00:08:14,140 --> 00:08:16,580
This is a legacy

140
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,300
that Mr. Tu and I

141
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,220
carry on from our master.

142
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,780
All the money comes
from everyone's donations.

143
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:24,980
It was meant to

144
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:26,620
support each other

145
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:28,140
in tough times.

146
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,420
I've kept doing this

147
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:32,780
over the years,

148
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:35,260
hoping to make up

149
00:08:36,380 --> 00:08:38,180
for the mistakes I made.

150
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:41,150
♪Only a blurry picture remains♪

151
00:08:41,740 --> 00:08:43,140
Sorry I've failed you.

152
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:44,880
♪Fading away bit by bit♪

153
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:51,900
What's so great about him?

154
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:53,260
I've been going up

155
00:08:53,260 --> 00:08:54,740
against Tu Hongjiang for years.

156
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:56,780
I know Tu way better than he does!

157
00:08:58,460 --> 00:08:59,700
Mr. Jiang

158
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:00,740
has connections everywhere

159
00:09:00,820 --> 00:09:02,100
and has been running wild for years.

160
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,020
He's definitely not simple.

161
00:09:04,140 --> 00:09:05,700
Not simple my foot!

162
00:09:06,220 --> 00:09:07,340
Always putting on airs with me!

163
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,140
He might be

164
00:09:09,420 --> 00:09:10,820
a big shot elsewhere.

165
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:11,780
But here in Xiatong,

166
00:09:12,180 --> 00:09:13,700
no one messes with me!

167
00:09:15,580 --> 00:09:16,740
Once I get close to him,

168
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:18,980
his spot

169
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:20,900
will eventually be mine!

170
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:25,380
- Pay us back!
- Pay us back!

171
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:27,380
When are you going to pay what you owe?

172
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:32,060
- Pay us back!
- Pay us back!

173
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:32,980
[Han Group]
Everyone!

174
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:33,460
- Pay us back!
- Pay us back!

175
00:09:33,460 --> 00:09:35,260
Calm down, everyone!

176
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:36,940
Stay calm, everyone!

177
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:39,460
We will make this right.

178
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,060
Once Mr. Han's daughter gets here,

179
00:09:41,180 --> 00:09:43,220
we'll have a solution.

180
00:09:43,220 --> 00:09:43,740
Alright?

181
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:44,780
We don't need that!

182
00:09:44,780 --> 00:09:45,980
We want our money now!

183
00:09:45,980 --> 00:09:46,500
Give me back my money!

184
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:51,060
- Pay us back!
- Pay us back!

185
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:51,820
Ms. Han is here.

186
00:09:53,180 --> 00:09:54,140
Ms. Han,

187
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:55,860
a man's dead, but his debts aren't!

188
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,260
This is our hard-earned money!

189
00:09:58,260 --> 00:09:59,060
Exactly!

190
00:09:59,420 --> 00:10:00,820
You've got to give us an answer.

191
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:02,340
How do we get our money back?

192
00:10:02,340 --> 00:10:05,140
- Answer us!
- Answer us!

193
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:05,820
- Pay us back!
- Pay us back!

194
00:10:05,820 --> 00:10:06,260
Yeah!

195
00:10:06,260 --> 00:10:07,020
- Pay us back!
- Pay us back!

196
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:08,020
Calm down.

197
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:09,260
Calm down!

198
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:14,500
[Han Group]
I'll repay every debt

199
00:10:14,940 --> 00:10:15,540
my father owed!

200
00:10:18,940 --> 00:10:20,100
If you don't believe me,

201
00:10:20,460 --> 00:10:21,740
I'll write new IOUs.

202
00:10:22,180 --> 00:10:23,940
You'll really write new IOUs?

203
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:24,740
When?

204
00:10:24,740 --> 00:10:25,700
Yeah, when?

205
00:10:25,940 --> 00:10:26,940
I'll do it today.

206
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:27,860
Alright.

207
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:28,780
Mr. Wang,

208
00:10:29,060 --> 00:10:30,100
take them to the finance office.

209
00:10:31,860 --> 00:10:32,660
Follow me.

210
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:34,460
One at a time.

211
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,780
One at a time. Take it easy.

212
00:10:43,140 --> 00:10:43,940
Tu,

213
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:47,780
what's your take on Han Weidong's death?

214
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:50,020
Based on the scene investigation,

215
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:52,660
homicide's been ruled out.

216
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:56,500
I don't believe he'd jump
to escape his problems.

217
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,660
You're saying someone pushed him to it?

218
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:04,100
Weidong and I met back in the army.

219
00:11:05,620 --> 00:11:06,780
He had no means,

220
00:11:07,420 --> 00:11:08,600
and it was impossible for him

221
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,920
to get involved
with drug trafficking on his own.

222
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:13,340
Not long after he left the force,

223
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:14,580
he started his company.

224
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:17,180
He said

225
00:11:17,180 --> 00:11:19,020
he made his money in transport.

226
00:11:20,540 --> 00:11:22,020
I didn't think too much about it.

227
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:23,500
I was just happy for him.

228
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:26,020
But later, I thought about it.

229
00:11:26,540 --> 00:11:30,140
There's no way he could have made
that much money

230
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:31,700
that fast

231
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:33,380
just from transport.

232
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:35,900
And during that time,

233
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:37,420
he was drinking a lot.

234
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:38,300
Right?

235
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:41,220
He seemed deeply preoccupied.

236
00:11:43,340 --> 00:11:45,540
If I'd been there for him more,

237
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:47,500
maybe none of this would've happened.

238
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,700
I know you two had a special bond.

239
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:53,540
But Han Weidong was in the wrong.

240
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,380
This isn't on you.

241
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,660
We joined the army

242
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,660
and became cops together.

243
00:12:04,460 --> 00:12:06,260
He never should've turned to drugs.

244
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:08,220
What a pity.

245
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:11,020
I know you wanted
to take the fall for him.

246
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:14,380
So, you insisted you were the one
who fired that shot.

247
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,300
And Han Weidong?

248
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:18,700
From what I've learned,

249
00:12:19,140 --> 00:12:21,660
he was too shocked

250
00:12:21,820 --> 00:12:23,220
to speak.

251
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,420
If not

252
00:12:25,420 --> 00:12:27,100
for your gun records,

253
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:28,780
I think he

254
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:31,180
would have just

255
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:33,180
let you take the fall for him.

256
00:12:37,380 --> 00:12:38,740
His family was struggling.

257
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:41,860
He needed the job more than I did.

258
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:43,980
No matter what his reasons were,

259
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,820
he shouldn't have turned
to drug trafficking.

260
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:49,660
And he kept at it for years.

261
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,180
No remorse.

262
00:12:51,700 --> 00:12:54,100
He was driven by greed.

263
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:56,780
No excuse for that.

264
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:05,420
Have some water.

265
00:13:11,980 --> 00:13:13,740
So, this is the situation.

266
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:15,460
All our accounts have been frozen.

267
00:13:16,180 --> 00:13:18,220
There's no cash left
to pay the salaries.

268
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:24,180
Contact the bank for me.

269
00:13:24,460 --> 00:13:26,220
I can take out a mortgage on the house.

270
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,340
We need to pay the employees
what they're owed.

271
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:29,180
Don't you know

272
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:30,540
the property and company assets

273
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:31,780
are already mortgaged?

274
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,460
Everything's mortgaged?

275
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:36,420
Then where did the money go?

276
00:13:38,100 --> 00:13:40,500
It was all used
for the company's daily operations.

277
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:48,700
Fine.

278
00:13:49,540 --> 00:13:50,820
I'll figure something else out.

279
00:14:02,460 --> 00:14:03,860
I want to work at the company.

280
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:04,980
Is that okay?

281
00:14:07,860 --> 00:14:09,060
Of course.

282
00:14:09,220 --> 00:14:10,540
It's your family's company.

283
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:11,540
But

284
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,180
what about your current job?

285
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:15,500
I'll handle it.

286
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:41,740
Mr. Jiang,

287
00:14:42,380 --> 00:14:43,300
you were right.

288
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:44,780
Sanmahu

289
00:14:44,780 --> 00:14:46,100
is furious that you won't let him

290
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:46,980
touch Tu Hongjiang.

291
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:48,820
People from the company
have been called in

292
00:14:48,820 --> 00:14:51,100
for questioning at the police station.

293
00:14:51,340 --> 00:14:53,020
I just got back from being questioned.

294
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:55,100
Time's running out.

295
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:57,500
Since he's in such a hurry to die,

296
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,500
give him a push.

297
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,780
Keep an eye on him.

298
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:03,500
Update me anytime.

299
00:15:05,460 --> 00:15:06,220
Understood.

300
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:19,820
- Mr. Wang.
- Mr. Wang.

301
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:20,660
Working late?

302
00:15:55,220 --> 00:15:56,140
Were you looking for me?

303
00:16:05,820 --> 00:16:08,260
Told you to go to the northern frontier
and clean up the mess.

304
00:16:10,140 --> 00:16:11,300
Why haven't you left?

305
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:14,420
I was supposed to leave tonight.

306
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:16,900
But I heard something.

307
00:16:18,420 --> 00:16:19,300
I'd like to talk to you about it.

308
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:27,980
Mr. Jiang.

309
00:16:29,860 --> 00:16:31,900
I'm telling you the truth.

310
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,300
Do you think it's possible?

311
00:16:35,820 --> 00:16:36,900
I see.

312
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:39,860
So you want to take over
Han Weidong's operations.

313
00:16:40,780 --> 00:16:41,820
I don't have that kind of ambition.

314
00:16:43,060 --> 00:16:44,100
I just want to

315
00:16:44,740 --> 00:16:46,060
help you

316
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:47,780
manage part of the business.

317
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:49,980
Someone else has already volunteered.

318
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:51,780
You

319
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:52,860
don't need to worry about this.

320
00:16:56,820 --> 00:16:58,660
Are you handing it all over to Sanmahu?

321
00:17:03,980 --> 00:17:05,460
Mr. Han and I

322
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:08,020
built this territory
in Xiatong together.

323
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,300
We figured out

324
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,220
the northern frontier route bit by bit.

325
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:13,580
You're just gonna
let Sanmahu take it all?

326
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:16,820
That doesn't seem right.

327
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:20,260
With Han Weidong dead,
this matter is settled.

328
00:17:20,660 --> 00:17:22,540
Drug trafficking is too dangerous.

329
00:17:23,300 --> 00:17:25,780
Go to the northern frontier
and take over the Han family's mines.

330
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:27,980
Then you can go straight.

331
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:34,020
I know you're looking out for me.

332
00:17:35,740 --> 00:17:36,500
But

333
00:17:36,740 --> 00:17:39,260
I don't know the first thing
about mining.

334
00:17:39,260 --> 00:17:41,620
Five years ago,
you didn't know anything either.

335
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,620
Now you run

336
00:17:44,020 --> 00:17:44,980
all of Xiatong's operations.

337
00:17:45,380 --> 00:17:46,180
So,

338
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:47,140
don't underestimate

339
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:48,900
your ability to start over.

340
00:17:50,980 --> 00:17:51,900
Impossible.

341
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:54,500
If I get caught now,

342
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:55,780
I'm dead for sure.

343
00:17:55,940 --> 00:17:57,580
There's no going straight for me.

344
00:17:57,940 --> 00:17:59,540
As long as you're not caught,

345
00:17:59,780 --> 00:18:00,900
there's still a chance.

346
00:18:01,420 --> 00:18:02,980
I'm not giving

347
00:18:03,340 --> 00:18:05,420
Xiatong's operations to Sanmahu.

348
00:18:05,980 --> 00:18:07,980
I'm getting out for good.

349
00:18:16,580 --> 00:18:18,500
If that's the case,

350
00:18:20,220 --> 00:18:21,620
then I guess I have to give up.

351
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,580
But

352
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:25,460
if I get caught someday

353
00:18:26,060 --> 00:18:27,780
and can't hold out, and end up

354
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:29,500
telling the cops about you...

355
00:18:39,780 --> 00:18:40,700
Are you threatening me?

356
00:18:45,380 --> 00:18:46,820
I just want a chance

357
00:18:48,100 --> 00:18:49,980
to control my own fate.

358
00:18:51,620 --> 00:18:52,940
I won't let you down.

359
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:13,580
Fine.

360
00:19:15,060 --> 00:19:15,940
I'll give you

361
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:18,340
a fair shot against Sanmahu.

362
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:21,660
May the best man win.

363
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:24,620
You'll have to live
with the consequences.

364
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:36,420
Uncle.

365
00:19:36,820 --> 00:19:38,180
I went through

366
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:39,140
Mabao's list again.

367
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:40,580
A few got caught.

368
00:19:40,580 --> 00:19:41,580
A few ran.

369
00:19:41,940 --> 00:19:43,340
Only three are left.

370
00:19:43,780 --> 00:19:45,420
They say the heat's too intense now,

371
00:19:45,860 --> 00:19:46,740
so they're afraid to take the goods.

372
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:48,020
What do we do?

373
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:49,980
It's good that they're afraid.

374
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:52,900
Anyone bold enough to ask for that much

375
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:56,180
is either trying to screw us over,

376
00:19:56,660 --> 00:19:57,540
or

377
00:19:58,660 --> 00:20:00,340
is a cop's informant.

378
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:07,300
Hello?

379
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:08,060
Mr. Sanmahu,

380
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:09,420
Elder Sun

381
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:11,500
from the Da'an League just sent word.

382
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:14,340
Says Qi Lianshan's nephew,

383
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:16,140
Qi Fengzi, wants to join us.

384
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:17,580
Asks if we'll take him in.

385
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:19,660
He says he'll vouch for him.

386
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:22,260
If Elder Sun vouches for him,
we can't say no.

387
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:23,460
Well,

388
00:20:23,980 --> 00:20:26,100
put him under you.

389
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:28,420
Keep an eye on him for three months.

390
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:29,740
If he's got what it takes,

391
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:31,260
send him

392
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:33,380
to the northern frontier

393
00:20:34,180 --> 00:20:35,660
to take back

394
00:20:35,660 --> 00:20:36,580
Qi Lianshan's turf.

395
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:37,420
Understood.

396
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:50,380
♪I stand upon the tower wall♪

397
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:52,820
♪To see the mountains tall♪

398
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:55,580
♪Outside the gate, I hear the sound♪

399
00:21:03,660 --> 00:21:06,020
♪Of chaos♪

400
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:07,700
♪All around♪

401
00:21:08,380 --> 00:21:10,220
The Dragon Unleashed
drug trafficking ring

402
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:11,900
in Xiatong has been basically wiped out.

403
00:21:12,380 --> 00:21:13,860
Only Sun Bojun remains at large.

404
00:21:14,020 --> 00:21:15,420
He goes by Mr. Sun.

405
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:16,100
Sir,

406
00:21:16,420 --> 00:21:17,980
has the merged case report

407
00:21:17,980 --> 00:21:19,220
I submitted

408
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:20,740
on Sanmahu's criminal group
been approved yet?

409
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:21,980
Mr. Tai approved.

410
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:23,500
The official documents

411
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,780
will be issued to Xiatong today.

412
00:21:25,460 --> 00:21:27,060
It's merged into the joint task force.

413
00:21:27,180 --> 00:21:28,860
You and Zhang Cheng
will remain in charge.

414
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:31,700
Call me if you need

415
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:33,100
any coordination.

416
00:21:33,220 --> 00:21:34,100
Got it.

417
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,100
Thanks.

418
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:43,260
Mr. Tu.

419
00:21:58,580 --> 00:21:59,500
Any news?

420
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:01,860
East suburbs.

421
00:22:01,860 --> 00:22:03,300
Around the Shisitiao area, Wuliying.

422
00:22:04,460 --> 00:22:05,380
That's as specific

423
00:22:05,540 --> 00:22:06,540
as it gets.

424
00:22:07,780 --> 00:22:08,580
Alright.

425
00:22:09,860 --> 00:22:11,660
Leave the rest to me.

426
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,980
Not a single one.

427
00:22:18,820 --> 00:22:19,780
What's going on

428
00:22:19,780 --> 00:22:21,140
with you today, old timer?

429
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:26,860
Haven't fished in a while, maybe.

430
00:22:27,820 --> 00:22:29,020
Or maybe I'm just getting old.

431
00:22:32,420 --> 00:22:33,420
What happened?

432
00:22:34,540 --> 00:22:35,340
Nothing.

433
00:22:36,140 --> 00:22:36,860
Nothing.

434
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:40,580
Mr. Tu.

435
00:22:42,180 --> 00:22:43,940
Lately, I've been
really missing my hometown.

436
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:46,460
I want to go back for a visit.

437
00:22:47,980 --> 00:22:49,060
I remember

438
00:22:50,820 --> 00:22:52,340
you have no family left there, right?

439
00:22:54,140 --> 00:22:55,380
Yes.

440
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:57,780
I left at fourteen,

441
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:00,620
and never planned to go back.

442
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:04,420
Lately, I don't know why,

443
00:23:05,540 --> 00:23:06,940
but I keep dreaming about the place.

444
00:23:08,660 --> 00:23:10,700
It's where I was born and raised.

445
00:23:15,020 --> 00:23:16,140
To return to one's roots, I guess.

446
00:23:17,380 --> 00:23:19,180
Feels like it's time to go back.

447
00:23:24,060 --> 00:23:25,260
For the first time,

448
00:23:27,420 --> 00:23:28,900
I've felt like I've lived a long life.

449
00:23:29,340 --> 00:23:31,420
You're saying that

450
00:23:32,020 --> 00:23:34,780
in front of an old man like me?

451
00:23:36,620 --> 00:23:38,100
It feels long enough.

452
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,460
All my old friends are gone,

453
00:23:41,580 --> 00:23:42,740
one by one.

454
00:23:44,020 --> 00:23:45,420
Especially Mr. Qian.

455
00:23:46,180 --> 00:23:47,660
He helped so many people,

456
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:50,420
and did so much good.

457
00:23:50,780 --> 00:23:51,900
But he didn't meet a good end.

458
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:54,580
Mr. Tu.

459
00:23:56,500 --> 00:23:57,940
Is this how it ends

460
00:23:58,940 --> 00:24:00,500
for people like us?

461
00:24:08,820 --> 00:24:10,420
What goes around, comes around.

462
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:13,180
Don't overthink it.

463
00:24:16,740 --> 00:24:18,140
Let me know before you leave.

464
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:20,380
We'll get together.

465
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:25,860
These gatherings

466
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:26,740
are numbered now.

467
00:24:45,220 --> 00:24:45,980
I understand.

468
00:24:46,380 --> 00:24:47,500
Send me the materials later.

469
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:50,340
I'll let you know when I receive them.

470
00:24:50,740 --> 00:24:51,580
Alright, that's it.

471
00:24:57,540 --> 00:24:58,140
Han Xin.

472
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:09,020
I'm leaving.

473
00:25:12,820 --> 00:25:14,100
I wanted to

474
00:25:14,260 --> 00:25:15,660
say goodbye to Mr. Tu and the others,

475
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:17,460
but they're all out on missions.

476
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,100
Wait a moment.

477
00:25:30,660 --> 00:25:31,740
All packed?

478
00:25:33,180 --> 00:25:34,060
Yes.

479
00:25:34,220 --> 00:25:35,100
I forgot something,

480
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:36,140
so I came back to get it.

481
00:25:40,300 --> 00:25:41,380
Is it because of your father?

482
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:44,220
Not entirely.

483
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:46,900
There are issues he left behind

484
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:48,060
that I need to resolve.

485
00:25:48,700 --> 00:25:50,220
But my role as a cop
doesn't allow it.

486
00:25:51,740 --> 00:25:53,220
Resigning

487
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:54,300
is my best option.

488
00:25:56,340 --> 00:25:57,140
Han Xin,

489
00:25:58,260 --> 00:25:59,060
you are you.

490
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:00,260
And your father is your father.

491
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:03,220
Some things are clearly right or wrong
in the eyes of the law.

492
00:26:03,420 --> 00:26:05,540
Some are judged by morality.

493
00:26:05,900 --> 00:26:07,060
You don't have to carry this alone.

494
00:26:07,260 --> 00:26:09,260
And you shouldn't
bear the weight of his mistakes.

495
00:26:12,260 --> 00:26:12,980
Mr. Zhan.

496
00:26:14,700 --> 00:26:16,540
I know your father was a hero

497
00:26:17,020 --> 00:26:17,820
and a martyr.

498
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:19,180
You're stepping

499
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:21,460
into the responsibility
and mission he left behind.

500
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:23,180
So am I.

501
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:27,100
Though my father's gone,

502
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,180
the company remains.

503
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:30,060
So do the responsibilities he left.

504
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:31,620
I have to take them on.

505
00:26:33,140 --> 00:26:34,260
No matter the outcome,

506
00:26:34,780 --> 00:26:35,700
I'll face it.

507
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:37,100
Han Xin,

508
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:38,460
remember this.

509
00:26:39,300 --> 00:26:40,460
Your colleagues here

510
00:26:40,540 --> 00:26:42,460
will always be your comrades
and friends.

511
00:26:42,860 --> 00:26:43,820
If you run into trouble,

512
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:44,980
come to us.

513
00:26:49,860 --> 00:26:50,900
There's something

514
00:26:51,060 --> 00:26:52,020
I need to ask of you.

515
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:52,900
Go ahead.

516
00:26:53,780 --> 00:26:55,100
I know the evidence
at the scene suggests

517
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:56,100
my father killed himself.

518
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:58,420
But I firmly believe
he wouldn't do that.

519
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,060
I will find proof.

520
00:27:00,340 --> 00:27:01,740
Please don't give up on this, alright?

521
00:27:04,020 --> 00:27:06,180
We still haven't caught Sanmahu
and Sun Bojun.

522
00:27:06,860 --> 00:27:08,260
As long as there's the slightest doubt,

523
00:27:08,340 --> 00:27:09,860
we'll never close the case.

524
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:13,340
That's good.

525
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:16,980
Mr. Zhan!

526
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:22,040
♪How could I accept fading away?♪

527
00:27:22,260 --> 00:27:24,220
Thank you for looking out for me.

528
00:27:24,220 --> 00:27:26,340
♪Drifting with
the ocean's rise and fall♪

529
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:27,260
Thank you, too.

530
00:27:28,060 --> 00:27:28,660
Take care.

531
00:27:30,000 --> 00:27:34,520
♪After the sea has eroded all traces♪

532
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:39,600
♪Silence returns to claim it all♪

533
00:27:39,820 --> 00:27:44,460
♪Counting the belated realizations now♪

534
00:27:44,460 --> 00:27:45,140
Mr. Zhan.

535
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:47,300
Stay safe on your mission.

536
00:27:47,700 --> 00:27:48,580
Protect yourself.

537
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:51,760
♪If only the roles could be rewritten♪

538
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:56,240
♪We'd lean less on illusions' glow♪

539
00:27:56,640 --> 00:28:01,200
♪To find the grace to let you go♪

540
00:28:24,140 --> 00:28:26,220
This place is hard to find.

541
00:28:26,540 --> 00:28:27,220
Where are you?

542
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:29,220
Bridge. There's a bridge.

543
00:28:30,940 --> 00:28:31,940
Alright.

544
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:52,780
Over here.

545
00:28:53,100 --> 00:28:54,460
I've been looking for you forever.

546
00:29:53,620 --> 00:29:54,660
Police! Freeze!

547
00:30:50,140 --> 00:30:50,700
Mr. Tu.

548
00:30:53,660 --> 00:30:54,420
Cuff him.

549
00:30:57,500 --> 00:30:58,060
Let's go.

550
00:31:09,100 --> 00:31:09,980
Be gentle.

551
00:31:09,980 --> 00:31:10,540
Behave.

552
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:15,700
Xin.

553
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:18,700
I suppose I should call you Ms. Han now.

554
00:32:19,380 --> 00:32:21,500
These are the financial statements
from all the subsidiaries.

555
00:32:22,300 --> 00:32:24,700
Except for Dasheng Transport,
which is still under seizure,

556
00:32:24,700 --> 00:32:26,340
the others are operating normally.

557
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:27,700
Take a look first.

558
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:30,020
Let me know if you have any questions.

559
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:33,380
Thanks.

560
00:32:34,260 --> 00:32:35,300
Thanks to you,

561
00:32:35,900 --> 00:32:37,020
the company is still running

562
00:32:38,100 --> 00:32:39,140
and the employees can keep their jobs.

563
00:32:39,940 --> 00:32:40,740
Don't mention it.

564
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:42,540
Mr. Han has always been good to me.

565
00:32:42,860 --> 00:32:44,420
When I came back from the south,

566
00:32:44,740 --> 00:32:45,500
my business had failed.

567
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:46,980
If Mr. Han hadn't given me a hand,

568
00:32:47,460 --> 00:32:49,700
I'd be working
on an assembly line somewhere.

569
00:32:50,460 --> 00:32:51,940
Even though he's gone,

570
00:32:52,340 --> 00:32:54,620
I'll make sure
to keep the company in good shape.

571
00:32:55,820 --> 00:32:56,500
By the way,

572
00:32:56,700 --> 00:32:58,380
this was Mr. Han's office.

573
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:00,060
It was just unsealed when you arrived.

574
00:33:00,060 --> 00:33:01,260
Haven't had time to tidy up.

575
00:33:01,580 --> 00:33:02,780
Let me know if you
have any concerns about it.

576
00:33:03,500 --> 00:33:05,900
Should we bring in
a feng shui consultant?

577
00:33:06,020 --> 00:33:07,780
Or maybe move to a different office?

578
00:33:07,980 --> 00:33:08,860
No need.

579
00:33:09,100 --> 00:33:09,940
I used to be a cop.

580
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:10,740
I'm as tough as nails.

581
00:33:11,780 --> 00:33:12,580
